									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>My complaint about edibles is that they take so long to kick in, which can be frustrating when you just want pain or nausea relief. (For that matter, there&#8217;s a learning curve for effective vaping, although it&#8217;s quicker.) But the first pass effect doesn&#8217;t knock out near as much THC as the amount you lose by inhaling &#8211; 90% of any inhaled meds get lost on the way to your lungs, leaving a mere wimpy 10% behind to do its job. And effects from edibles do seem to stick around longer, without vaping side effects. </p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-1316296" class="comment odd alt depth-4 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-1316296" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/ee6c6379888f8edcd9b1bd4754c62c98?s=74&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/ee6c6379888f8edcd9b1bd4754c62c98?s=148&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-74 photo' height='74' width='74' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://www.xeni.net/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Xeni Jardin</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

