				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>All this means is that there are no big pharma funded double-blind studies on this, and why would there be? The word &#8220;anecdotal&#8221; gets a bad rap. I think something like 10,000 anecdotes equal the same margin of error of a double-blind study. Low-dose naltrexone suffers the same dismissive attitude by the western medicine community. It&#8217;s still more effective for a huge number of auto-immune, cancer, and other patients than any other drug or combination of treatments they&#8217;ve been prescribed by traditional doctors. I know from experience.</p>
